nell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/paraman1/paraman1_26_03_01_5/DSP_P6224584.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/paraman1/paraman1_26_03_01_5/DSP_P6224585.jpg"]}]}, {"genus": "Rourea", "authors": "Aubl.", "last_edited": "Last edited by Pieter B. Pelser, 1 September 2023", "species": [{"u": 2343, "scientific_name": "Rourea minor", "taxon_name": "Rourea minor", "category": "", "status": "Native.", "citation": "(Gaertn.) Merr. , Interpr. Herb. Amboin. (1917) 413 ; Leenhouts, Fl. Males. ser. 1, 5 (1958) 514; Romeroso et al., J. Asia-Pacific Biodiv. 17 (2024) 10; ≡ Aegiceras minus Gaertn. , Fruct. Sem. Pl. 1 (1788) 216. = Santaloides erecta (Blanco) G.Schellenb. , Mitt. Bot. Mus. Univ. Zürich 50 (1910) 52; ≡ Rourea erecta (Blanco) Merr. , PJS 4c (1909) 125 ; Fl. Manila (1912) 220; Merrill, EPFP 2 (1923) 239; ≡ Cnestis erecta Blanco , Fl. Filip., 1st Ed. (1837) 387. = Rourea imbricata Elmer , LPB 7 (1915) 2597 ; Merrill, EPFP 2 (1923) 240; Type: Elmer 14309 (NA, iso; but replicates also distributed as ‘13951’ in L, MO, NY, US). = Rourea luzoniensis Merr. , PJS 14 (1919) 404 ; Merrill, EPFP 2 (1923) 240. = Rourea unifoliolata Merr. , PJS 8c (1913) 372 ; Merrill, EPFP 2 (1923) 240. = Rourea volubilis Merr. , Publ. Bur. Sci. Gov. Lab. 27 (1905) 36 ; Merrill, EPFP 2 (1923) 240.", "distribution": "Africa, Andaman Isls, Australia, Bangladesh, Borneo, Cambodia, China, Hong Kong, India, Java, Laos, Lesser Sunda Isls, Madagascar, Malay Peninsula, Moluccas, Myanmar, New Caledonia, New Guinea, Nicobar Isls, Pacific Ocean, Philippines, Solomon Isls, Sri Lanka, Sulawesi, Sumatra, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam. BALABAC, BANTAYAN, BASILAN, BILIRAN, CAMIGUIN, CATANDUANES, CULION, CUYO, CUYO ARCHIPELAGO, DINAGAT, HOMONHON, LEYTE, LUBANG, LUZON: Albay, Bataan, Batangas, Cagayan, Camarines Norte, Camarines Sur, Ilocos Norte, La Union, Laguna, NCR, Pangasinan, Quezon, Rizal, Sorsogon, Zambales, MINDANAO: Agusan, Agusan del Norte, Davao del Sur, Lanao del Sur, Surigao, MINDORO, PALAWAN, PAMALICAN, PANAY, POLILLO, SAMAR.", "notes": "P.B. Pelser (6-May-2022): this appears to be a different species than Cnestis volubilis Blanco, but I don't know what species the latter name refers to. Widespread throughout the Philippines ; in primary and secondary forests, dry thickets, also more open places and along riverbanks. Usually a large liana, rarely shrub or treelet. 0-1800m.", "conservation_status": "", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/bhbase/cubic_gallery_public.pl?start_at=0&taxon_name=Rourea+minor", "thumbs": ["http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8841.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8838.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8840.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8839.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8837.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8844.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8842.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8845.jpg.400.jpg"], "full": ["http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8841.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8838.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8840.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8839.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/8_10_15/10Aug15/DSC_8837.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoima